title: Arizona State holds on late, upsets No. 7 UCLA 38-23 (Yahoo Sports)
text: Posts: 54,046 Arizona State holds on late, upsets No. 7 UCLA 38-23 (Yahoo Sports) Mike Bercovici passed for 273 yards and two touchdowns and ran for another score, and Arizona State got its season back on track with a 38-23 victory over No. 7 UCLA on Saturday night. Tim White and D.J. Foster caught scoring passes for the Sun Devils (3-2, 1-1 Pac-12), who responded to their dire situation after two September losses with a solid effort in their second straight win at the Rose Bowl. Arizona State built a 29-10 lead heading into the fourth quarter and then hung on.
